The paper deals with designing succinct data structures for interval graphs and their variants, which is a topic in data structures (cs.DS) and computational geometry (cs.CG). The paper also discusses various combinatorial algorithms on these graphs, which falls under the category of discrete mathematics (cs.DM). The paper's focus on optimizing queries and running times suggests that it may also be relevant to the sub-categories of algorithms and complexity (cs.CC) and distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DL).
